<section xml:id="csp-collections-intro_in-and-not-in">
        <title>In and Not In</title>
        
        
        <p>To check if an item is in a list, we can use the <c>in</c> operator. To check if something is
            not in a list, we can use <c>not in</c>:</p>

    <program xml:id="cspcollectionsintro_listin1" interactive="activecode" language="python">
        <input>
inviteList = ["Dora", "Rex", "Humberto", "Devon"]

if "Dora" in inviteList:
    print("We invited Dora")

if "Joe" not in inviteList:
    print("We forgot to invite Joe")
        </input>
    </program>
        <p>Because <c>in</c> and <c>not in</c> are opposites, we can often use just one or the other and
            handle the other case with else:</p>

    <program xml:id="cspcollectionsintro_listin2" interactive="activecode" language="python">
        <input>
inviteList = ["Dora", "Rex", "Humberto", "Devon"]
name = input("Enter a name to check against the list:")

if name in inviteList:
    print("We invited", name)
else:
    print("We forgot", name)
        </input>
    </program>
    </section>

